    {
      "sort": 200000,
      "name": "Exhaustion",
      "type": "rule",
      "_id": "matJrnCondExhaus",
      "title": {
        "show": true,
        "level": 2
      },
      "image": {},
      "text": {
        "format": 1,
        "content": "<p>While you have the Exhaustion condition, you experience the following effects.</p><p><em><strong>Exhaustion Levels.</strong></em> This condition is cumulative. Each time you receive it, you gain 1 Exhaustion level. You die if your Exhaustion level is 6.</p><p><em><strong>D20 Tests Affected.</strong></em> When you make a &amp;Reference[D20 Test], the roll is reduced by 2 times your Exhaustion level.</p><p><em><strong>Imposed DCs Affected.</strong></em> All DCs that you impose are reduced by 2 times your Exhaustion level.</p><p><em><strong>Speed Reduced.</strong></em> Your &amp;Reference[Speed] is reduced by a number of feet equal to 5 times your Exhaustion level.</p><p><em><strong>Removing Exhaustion Levels.</strong></em> Finishing a &amp;Reference[Long Rest] removes 1 of your Exhaustion levels. When your Exhaustion level reaches 0, the condition ends.</p>",
        "markdown": ""
      },
