    {
      "sort": 350000,
      "name": "Prone",
      "type": "rule",
      "_id": "matJrnCondProne0",
      "title": {
        "show": true,
        "level": 2
      },
      "image": {},
      "text": {
        "format": 1,
        "content": "<ul><li>A prone creature's only movement option is to crawl, unless it stands up and thereby ends the condition.</li><li>The creature has Disadvantage on attack rolls.</li><li>An attack roll against the creature has Advantage if the attacker is within 5 feet of the creature. Otherwise, the attack roll has Disadvantage.</li><li>Standing from prone requires 15 feet of movement, or half its movement if the creature's total movement is less than 15 feet.</li><li>Standing from prone within reach of an enemy provokes an Opportunity Attack from that enemy.</li></ul>",
        "markdown": ""
      },
